    ["What is the first step of the accounting cycle?", "Analyze business transactions and source documents."],
    ["What comes after analyzing transactions?", "Journalize transactions in the general journal."],
    ["What is the third step in the accounting cycle?", "Post journal entries to the ledger accounts."],
    ["Scenario: A business receives a cash payment. What accounting cycle step is next?", "Journalize the transaction."],
    ["Step after posting to the ledger?", "Prepare an unadjusted trial balance."],
    ["Why prepare an unadjusted trial balance?", "To ensure total debits equal total credits before adjustments."],
    ["Next step after unadjusted trial balance?", "Journalize adjusting entries."],
    ["Scenario: Prepaid insurance has expired. Which accounting step is this?", "Prepare adjusting entries."],
    ["Step after recording adjusting entries?", "Post adjustments to the ledger accounts."],
    ["Why post adjustments?", "To update account balances before financial statements."],
    ["Next step after posting adjustments?", "Prepare an adjusted trial balance."],
    ["What is the purpose of an adjusted trial balance?", "To verify accounts are balanced and accurate for financial statements."],
    ["Step after adjusted trial balance?", "Prepare financial statements."],
    ["Which statements are prepared?", "Income statement, statement of owner’s equity, balance sheet, and sometimes cash flow statement."],
    ["Scenario: Net income is determined. Which step is this?", "Prepare financial statements."],
    ["Next step after financial statements?", "Journalize closing entries."],
    ["Why journalize closing entries?", "To transfer temporary account balances to owner’s equity and reset accounts for the next period."],
    ["Step after closing entries?", "Post closing entries to the ledger."],
    ["What is the final step of the accounting cycle?", "Prepare a post-closing trial balance."],
    ["Why prepare a post-closing trial balance?", "To ensure all temporary accounts are closed and the ledger is ready for the next period."],
    ["Scenario: All revenue and expense accounts have been zeroed. Which step?", "Post-closing trial balance."],
    ["Step before preparing financial statements?", "Post adjusting entries to the ledger."],
    ["Why is journalizing transactions critical?", "It provides a chronological record of all business activities."],
    ["Scenario: A business buys office supplies on credit. Which cycle step is this?", "Analyze and journalize the transaction."],
    ["Step to verify ledger accuracy?", "Prepare unadjusted trial balance."],
    ["Why are adjusting entries necessary?", "To account for accrued, deferred, or estimated items not yet recorded."],
    ["Scenario: Depreciation on equipment is recorded. Which step?", "Prepare adjusting entries."],
    ["Why close temporary accounts?", "To reset revenue and expense accounts for the new accounting period."],
    ["Scenario: Owner withdraws cash for personal use. Which accounting cycle step?", "Record closing entries to Drawing account."],
    ["Step that ensures debits equal credits after adjustments?", "Prepare adjusted trial balance."],
    ["Which step summarizes business performance for the period?", "Prepare financial statements."],
    ["Why is posting critical in the accounting cycle?", "It transfers journal entries to ledger accounts for accurate balances."],
    ["Scenario: Trial balance shows unequal debits and credits. Which step?", "Investigate and correct journal or posting errors."],
    ["Step that finalizes all account balances for reporting?", "Post-closing trial balance."],
    ["Scenario: Business prepares a balance sheet after closing entries. Which step?", "Post-closing trial balance confirms accuracy."],
    ["How many main steps are in the accounting cycle?", "Typically 10 steps from analyzing transactions to post-closing trial balance."]
