    ["What is an asset?", "A resource owned by a business that has economic value and can provide future benefits."],
    ["Scenario: Company buys a delivery truck. Is it an asset?", "Yes, the truck is a fixed asset providing future benefits."],
    ["What is a liability?", "A financial obligation or debt a business owes to an outside party."],
    ["Scenario: Company owes $1,000 to a supplier. Is this an asset or liability?", "Liability; it represents money owed."],
    ["What is accounts payable?", "Amounts a business owes to suppliers for goods or services received on credit."],
    ["Scenario: Company receives $500 of supplies on credit. What account increases?", "Accounts payable increases by $500."],
    ["What is accounts receivable?", "Amounts owed to a business by customers for goods or services sold on credit."],
    ["Scenario: Company sells $300 of merchandise on credit. Which account increases?", "Accounts receivable increases by $300."],
    ["What is owner’s equity?", "The residual interest in the assets of a business after deducting liabilities."],
    ["Scenario: Owner invests $2,000 cash. Which account increases?", "Owner’s equity increases $2,000."],
    ["What is revenue?", "Income earned from a business’s primary operations, like sales of goods or services."],
    ["Scenario: Company earns $1,500 from consulting. Which account increases?", "Revenue increases $1,500."],
    ["What is an expense?", "Costs incurred to generate revenue, decreasing owner’s equity."],
    ["Scenario: Company pays $200 for utilities. Which account decreases?", "Owner’s equity decreases via an expense account."],
    ["What is a withdrawal?", "Cash or assets taken out of the business by the owner for personal use."],
    ["Scenario: Owner takes $400 cash from the business. Which account is affected?", "Owner’s equity decreases via withdrawals."],
    ["What is a journal?", "A detailed record of all business transactions in chronological order."],
    ["Scenario: Recording a sale on account. Which accounting tool is used first?", "The journal."],
    ["What is a ledger?", "A collection of all accounts showing their balances and activity."],
    ["Scenario: Posting from the journal to the ledger. Purpose?", "To summarize transactions by account."],
    ["What is a trial balance?", "A list of all ledger accounts and their balances to check if debits equal credits."],
    ["Scenario: Debits do not equal credits. Which step?", "Check the trial balance for errors."],
    ["What is a general journal?", "A journal used to record all types of transactions in one place."],
    ["Scenario: Business records rent expense, purchase of equipment, and sales. Which journal?", "General journal."],
    ["What is a purchase account?", "An account used to track the cost of goods bought for resale."],
    ["Scenario: Company buys inventory for $800. Which account records this?", "Purchase account."],
    ["What is a sales account?", "An account recording income from selling goods or services."],
    ["Scenario: Company sells $1,000 of products. Which account increases?", "Sales account."],
    ["What is a cash account?", "An account that records all cash receipts and payments."],
    ["Scenario: Business receives $500 in cash from a customer. Which account?", "Cash account increases $500."],
    ["What is a prepaid expense?", "An asset representing payment made in advance for a future expense."],
    ["Scenario: Company pays $600 for 6 months of insurance. Which account?", "Prepaid insurance (asset) increases $600."],
    ["What is a note payable?", "A written promise to pay a specific amount of money on a future date."],
    ["Scenario: Company signs a $2,000 note for equipment. Which account?", "Notes payable (liability) increases $2,000."],
    ["What is a note receivable?", "A written promise from another party to pay the business a certain amount."],
    ["Scenario: Company receives a promissory note from a customer. Which account?", "Notes receivable (asset) increases."],
    ["What is a fixed asset?", "A long-term tangible asset used in operations, like buildings or equipment."],
    ["Scenario: Business buys a computer for office use. Which type of asset?", "Fixed asset."],
    ["What is a current asset?", "An asset expected to be converted to cash or used within one year."],
    ["Scenario: Company holds $2,000 in inventory. Type of asset?", "Current asset."]
