    ["Scenario: Prepaid expenses account has $600 debit. How should it appear on trial balance?", "Include $600 under debits in the trial balance."],
    ["How does a trial balance aid in preparing financial statements?", "It confirms that the ledger balances are correct, providing a foundation for income statements and balance sheets."],
    ["Scenario: Unequal trial balance totals after posting. How to fix?", "Trace each ledger balance back to journal entries to identify and correct errors."],
    ["Why list accounts in a specific order on a trial balance?", "Typically, assets, liabilities, equity, revenue, and expenses, to match the order of the balance sheet and income statement."],
    ["Scenario: Multiple accounts have zero balances. Should they appear on trial balance?", "Yes, to provide a complete record and verify that all accounts have been considered."]
